---

<Page
  title="About Us — Useless Today | The Curated Useless Web"
  description="About Useless Today: who we are and why we built a hand-picked wall of useless websites. Our small mission to make wasting time online a little kinder and a lot more fun."
  path="/about/"
  eyebrow="About us"
  heading="We make wasting time, beautifully."
  intro="Useless Today is a small, lovingly curated corner of the useless web — a wall of pointless websites that exist for no reason other than to make you smile."
  schema={schema}
>
  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    Useless Today started with a simple, slightly silly idea: the internet is
    full of <strong>useless websites</strong> — single-serving toys, daft
    experiments, and oddball little pages — and somebody should put the best of
    them in one place. Most "useless web" tools fling you off to one random page
    and leave you guessing. We wanted something kinder and more browsable: a
    whole wall you can scan by mood, search in a second, or hand over to fate
    with a single button.
  </p>
  <p>
    We're not a big company. We're a tiny project run by people who think the
    web was more fun when it was a little more pointless, and who believe a
    website that does exactly one silly thing perfectly is a genuine work of
    art.
  </p>

  <h2>What we believe</h2>
  <p>
    Not everything online needs to be productive. A <strong>useless day</strong> —
    or even a useless five minutes — is a small, free way to reset. We think
    there's real value in delight for its own sake, and we'd rather send you
    somewhere charming than somewhere "optimised."
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Hand-picked, not random.</strong> Every link on the wall is chosen by a human and checked regularly, so you never hit a dead end.</li>
    <li><strong>You always land back here.</strong> Every useless site opens in a new tab, so the rabbit hole never loses you.</li>
    <li><strong>No dark patterns.</strong> No autoplay traps, no endless pop-ups, no selling your data. Just pointless fun.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>
    Browse <a href="/#directory">the wall</a> and filter by Silly, Relaxing,
    Weird, Games, or Art. In a hurry to be entertained? Hit
    <strong>Surprise me</strong> and we'll open a fresh pointless site for you.
    There's also a new <em>Useless Today</em> pick at the top of the home page
    every day — the same surprise for everyone — and a counter that quietly
    tallies how gloriously you're wasting your time.
  </p>

  <h2>Get in touch</h2>
  <p>
    Found a wonderfully useless site we should add, or spotted a broken link?
    We'd love to hear from you — head over to our
    <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a> or email
    <a href="mailto:prasad.rajeshwar@gmail.com">prasad.rajeshwar@gmail.com</a>.
  </p>
</Page>
